# PROJECT: piper-poc

## Goal
Slint-baseret GUI til at teste piper1-gpl tekst-til-tale motoren via dens C API.
Brugeren skriver tekst, vælger stemme (dansk/engelsk) og hastighed, og hører resultatet.
Understøtter også WAV-eksport. Formålet er at evaluere piper1-gpl som TTS-backend.

## Stack
- Language: Rust 2024 edition
- UI: Slint 1.x (desktop)
- Audio: cpal 0.15 (playback), hound 3.5 (WAV export)
- TTS: piper1-gpl C API via FFI (piper.h)
- Build scanners: RulesTools (rustscan + slintscan + rustdocumenter)

## Structure
- ui:      ui/ (Slint files — globals, tokens, views, components)
- src:     src/ (Rust — adapter, core, gateway, shared)
- models:  models/ (ONNX voice models — da_DK, en_US)
- proj:    proj/
- tools:   tools/

## Method
- Workflow: PROJECT → FIXES → TODO → code → test → DONE
- Branching: feature branches off main
- Testing: cargo test + manual TTS playback
- Deploy: N/A (local PoC)

## Patterns
- piper-streaming: piper_synthesize_start → piper_synthesize_next loop for chunked audio
- ffi-safety: all piper C calls wrapped in safe Rust types in gateway layer

